```suggestion
understood as an operator `(V → E) → (W → E)`, where `V` and `W` are normed `ℝ`-vector spaces
```
why did you make L implicit for the next two lemmas ? I mean why for those two specifically, since all others have explicit L.
No good reason. I've made it explicit.
Do you know what takes so long?

In fact it's not needed for the current version of the proof, so I've removed it. It was needed when I was building the proof, maybe because I hadn't squizzed some simps. My guess is that it's due to typeclass inference, because we're dealing with complicated objects (spaces of continuous linear maps from spaces of continuous multilinear maps to other spaces, for instance).
This `simpa` is terminal and the expanded `simpa only` is rather long. Perhaps don't expand it, for readability? Unless its very slow that way.
